      "decision": "Insert conditional range validation AFTER resolve_probability_edit_base_marginals and BEFORE validate_structure_preserving_edit in normalize_probability_edit_payload (server.py ~line 3464-3469). Only runs when context is non-empty.",
      "based_on": ["q4"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "After validate_structure_preserving_edit — rejected because a tighter, earlier error is more informative",
        "As a separate pre-check during normalization — rejected because base marginals must be resolved first"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d4",
      "decision": "Compute admissible range locally from resolved base marginals using the proportional rescaling algorithm — no additional inference engine queries.",
      "based_on": ["q5", "q7"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Query inference engine for joint distribution constraints — rejected because the range is fully derivable from the conditional slice and rescaling algorithm (proportional rescaling preserves non-negativity for any p in (0,1) given valid base marginals)"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "d5",
      "decision": "Server-side validation only. Include admissible range in error details when rejecting. No new API endpoint; no frontend changes.",
      "based_on": ["q2"],
      "alternatives_rejected": [
        "Add a dedicated query endpoint for admissible range — rejected because T558 scope is enforcement, not API surface expansion. Frontend (T575) can adopt bounds from error details later.",
        "Modify ConditionalEditor.tsx slider bounds — rejected because T575 owns UI baseline changes"
      ],
      "reversibility": "easy"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "task": "Add compute_conditional_admissible_range() function in server.py. Takes market, target_outcome_id, and base_marginals. Returns {min, max} tuple. For proportional rescaling: structural min is a small epsilon above 0 (matching existing 0<p<1 check), structural max is 1-epsilon. Edge case: if all non-target base marginals are zero, range is exactly {1.0, 1.0} (target must be 1.0). Apply 12-decimal rounding tolerance for edge cases near 0 or 1.",
      "depends_on": []
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "task": "Add validate_conditional_range_bounds() function in server.py. Takes market, normalized_payload, and base_marginals. Calls compute_conditional_admissible_range(). If target probability is outside the admissible range, raises ApiError(400, 'conditional_range_violation', message, {min, max, marketId, outcomeId, requestedProbability}).",
      "depends_on": [1]
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "task": "Wire validate_conditional_range_bounds() into normalize_probability_edit_payload() at server.py:3469 (after base_marginals resolution, before validate_structure_preserving_edit). Only call when context is non-empty (conditional edit). Guard: if normalized_payload['context'] is truthy.",
      "depends_on": [2]
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "task": "Add unit tests for compute_conditional_admissible_range(): binary market normal case, N>2 outcomes, all-zero non-target marginals edge case, rounding edge cases near 0 and 1.",
      "depends_on": [1]
    },
    {
      "step": 5,
      "task": "Add integration tests for validate_conditional_range_bounds() through normalize_probability_edit_payload(): conditional edit within range succeeds, conditional edit outside range returns 400 with 'conditional_range_violation' and includes admissible range in details, unconditional edit bypasses the check entirely.",
      "depends_on": [3]
    }
  ],
  "spawn_children": false,
  "children": []
}

